<h2 id="scaling-considerations">📈 Scaling Considerations</h2>

What works at one location often breaks at five. Here's what we've learned about scaling med spa tech stacks:

**User Permission Complexity:** Single-location practices can get away with loose permission structures. Multi-location operations need role-based access that varies by site, preventing front desk staff at Location A from accessing patient records at Location B while allowing regional managers oversight across their territory.

**Reporting Consolidation:** Ownership needs unified dashboards showing all locations. Managers need filtered views of their sites only. Providers need their personal productivity metrics. Ensure your stack handles these varying perspectives without manual report building.

**Inventory Distribution:** Growing beyond one location introduces inventory transfer challenges. Can your system track product movement between sites? Handle different par levels based on location volume? Manage purchasing at corporate level while allowing location-level consumption tracking?

**Brand Consistency:** Multiple locations mean multiple opportunities for inconsistent client experiences. Your tech stack should enforce consistent intake forms, consent language, and communication templates across all sites.

We've covered multi-location operational challenges extensively in our [scaling service businesses guide](/guides/scaling-service-businesses-technology) which addresses these pain points in detail.

